            "creation_date": 1320853016,
            "body": "<p>you can use spring annotations too<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@Scheduled(cron=\"*/5 * * * * MON-FRI\")\npublic void doSomething() {\n// something that should execute on weekdays only\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/spring-framework-reference/html/scheduling.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/spring-framework-reference/html/scheduling.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8067406,
            "question_id": 8066141
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d72cd5dd252ead1c5648d9a00a5b8797?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 235224,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 501889,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/501889/theme",
                "reputation": 361,
                "display_name": "theme"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1349961526,
            "creation_date": 1347002637,
            "body": "<p>this is how I've solved it using java7SE:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    timer = new Timer(\"Timer\", true);\n    Calendar cr = Calendar.getInstance(TimeZone.getTimeZone(\"GMT\"));\n    cr.setTimeInMillis(System.currentTimeMillis());\n    long day = TimeUnit.DAYS.toMillis(1);\n    //Pay attention - Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY for 24h day model \n    //(Calendar.HOUR is 12h model, with p.m. a.m. )\n    cr.set(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY, it.getHours());\n    cr.set(Calendar.MINUTE, it.getMinutes());\n    long delay = cr.getTimeInMillis() - System.currentTimeMillis();\n    //insurance for case then time of task is before time of schedule\n    long adjustedDelay = (delay &gt; 0 ? delay : day + delay);\n    timer.scheduleAtFixedRate(new StartReportTimerTask(it), adjustedDelay, day);\n    //you can use this schedule instead is sure your time is after current time\n    //timer.scheduleAtFixedRate(new StartReportTimerTask(it), cr.getTime(), day);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>it happens to be trickier than I thought to do it correctly<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 12313590,
            "question_id": 8066141,
            "last_edit_date": 1349961526
        },
